Sony shares plunge in Tokyo trade after 
the company posts a $6.4 billion loss for the last fiscal year. 
Japan reports a surprise gain in machinery orders 
month-on-month. And Rick Santorum suspends his campaign for the 
GOP presidential nomination. Bloomberg's Susan Li reports. 
(Source: Bloomberg)  Running Time: 02:25
 